\cf0 \

\f1\b\fs28 1. Make internet connection for installation
\f0\b0\fs24 \
Connect Raspberry to Internet by Wifi or Ethernet\
\

\f1\b\fs28 2. Enable serial port
\f0\b0\fs24 \
In Raspberry Pi configuration -> interfaces\
- Enable Serial Port\
- Disable Serial Console\
\

\f1\b\fs28 3. Turn off pincode
\fs24 \

\f0\b0 This step only has to be done if the SIM card still has an active pincode\
Turning of the pincode is needed while the AT+CPIN command reply\'92s with OK to soon which will cause the chat script to go on before the modem is ready.\
\

\f1\b Install minicom\

\f0\b0 Terminal commands:
\f1\b \

\f0\b0 \cf2 sudo apt-get update\
sudo apt-get install minicom\
\

\f1\b \cf3 Connect to modem\

\f0\b0 \cf0 Terminal command:
\f1\b \cf3 \

\f0\b0 \cf2 sudo minicom -D /dev/ttyS0 -b 115200\
\cf0 \

\f1\b Turn off pincode in minicom\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 ATZ\cf4  \cf3 should return OK\cf4 \
